<TITLE> Ex-NBR member Sarwar sent to jail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 26 (bdnews24.com)  Former NBR member ATM Sarwar Hossain, convicted of tax-evasion and holding illegal assets, was sent to Dhaka Central Jail following his surrender in court Sunday morning. Sarwar was sentenced to a total of 21 years between 2007-08 in the two separate cases. A special court sentenced him to eight years on Sept 20, 2007, in a case filed by the National Board of Revenue for evading tax and providing fabricated information in his income tax return. He was convicted of concealing information about assets worth Tk 4.31 crore and evading related taxes. Sarwar was also sentenced to 13 years in jail by a special court in May 2008 in an illegal wealth case filed by Anticorruption Commission. He was convicted of amassing around Tk 1.5 crore beyond known sources of income and concealing information on Tk 1.34 crore in a wealth statement to the ACC. His wife Nazma Sarwar was also sentenced to three years in jail for abetting her husband. Sarwar's lawyer Prannath applied for his client's division in jail. Justice Sirajul Islam said that steps would be taken according to the prison code. bdnew
